Intro:

  A distributed sorter meant to sort large text files using various search algorithms at once, reporting their performance at the end.

Files:
	Makefile
	readme.txt
	splitmerge.c
	root.c
	shellsort.c
	bubblesort.c
	quicksort.c

Run With:
    ./sorter -d <depth> -f <file> -a <column 1 to 4>
  Note - In order to run the clean-up shell script, may have to
         enter :-  chmod -x *.sh

Problems:
  None known.

